al%20adjustments%2C%20weather%2C%20revisions%2C%20and%20strikes%20are%20all%20likely%20to%20impact%20the%20trend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20warm%20weather%20often%20helps%20boost%20seasonal%20employment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-weather-events-impact-el-nino-volatility-inflation-economy-2023-7%5C%22%3Ethis%20summer's%20extreme%20heat%20could%20have%20the%20opposite%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20outdoor%20venues%20likely%20suffered%20from%20fewer%20patrons%2C%20according%20to%20Kalish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESigns%20of%20a%20slowdown%20in%20job%20growth%20has%20been%20apparent%20over%20the%20past%20two%20months%2C%20as%20the%20three-month%20average%20of%20non-farm%20payroll%20additions%20has%20fallen%20by%2010%2C000%20each%20of%20the%20last%20two%20months.%20And%20the%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-market-hiring-july-unemployment-rate-2023-8%5C%22%3Emost%20recent%20job%20reports%20also%20came%20in%20below%20economist%20estimates%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20ending%20a%20more%20than%20year-long%20streak%20of%20better-than-expected%20job%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%20that%20could%20limit%20future%20job%20growth%20includes%20tighter%20lending%20standards%20and%20a%20potential%20strike%20by%20the%20UAW%20and%20other%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20decline%20in%20the%20average%20workweek%20is%20another%20leading%20indicator%20that%20has%20been%20moving%20lower%20more%20recently.%20That's%20not%20a%20good%20sign%20for%20employer's%20future%20hiring%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20prefer%20to%20reduce%20hours%20rather%20than%20cut%20headcount.%20But%20at%20some%20point%20further%20workweek%20reductions%20become%20impractical%20and%20layoffs%20pick%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalish%20said.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20stop%20hiring%20before%20they%20start%20firing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20many%20stock%20market%20bulls%20pointing%20to%20%