2%A0and%20it%20will%20be%20hard%20to%20design%20government%20programs%20to%20help.%3Cp%3EBrendan%20McDermid%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENobel-Prize%20winning%20economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fpaul-krugman%5C%22%3EPaul%20Krugman%3C%2Fa%3E%20appeared%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20Odd%20Lots%20podcast%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKrugman%20talked%20about%20AI's%20potential%20to%20displace%20white-collar%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20contended%20that%20there%20isn't%20much%20the%20government%20can%20do%20to%20mitigate%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-at-risk-from-ai-replace-change-chatgpt-automation-study-2023-7%5C%22%3Eboom%20in%20AI%20might%20wipe%20out%20your%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there%20may%20not%20be%20much%20we%20can%20do%20about%20that%2C%20Nobel-Prize%20winning%20economist%20Paul%20Krugman%20said%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-11%2Fpaul-krugman-on-why-alien-invasions-are-inflationary-transcript%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepisode%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bloomberg's%20Odd%20Lots%20podcast%20on%20Friday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-economy-federal-reserve-interest-rates-hikes-pandemic-recombobulation-2023-7%5C%22%3EKrugman%2C%20who%20regularly%20writes%20about%20economic%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20broader%20impact%2C%20said%20he%20thinks%20AI%20is%20%26quot%3Btoo%20pervasive%20and%20too%20diffuse%26quot%3B%20to%20warrant%20any%20major%20intervention%20from%20the%20government.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhat%20he%20means%20is%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-white-collar-jobs-at-risk-artificial-intelligence-ai-2023-2%5C%22%3EAI%20boom%20is%20likely%20to%20wipe%20out%20some%20white-collar%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(over%20manual-labor%20jobs)%20evenly%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20devastating%20one%20particular%20region%20or%20social%20group.%20That%20means%20it'll%20be%20hard%20to%20design%20remedial%20policies%2C%20he%20says%2C%20to%20help%20displaced%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20there's%20much%20you%20can%20do%20about%20that%20aside%20from%20just%20trying%20to%20ban%20the%20technology%20altogether%2C%20which%20isn't%20going%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrugman%20contended%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20white-collar%20work%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%3Etools%20like%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20threatening%2C%20though%2C%20isn't%20rooted%20in%20creative%20or%20original%20thinking.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20many%20people%20out%20there%20in%20the%20real%20world%20are%20in%20fact%20being%20creative%3F%20How%20much%20of%20the%20work%20that%20we%20pay%20people%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20do%20is%20in%20fact%20a%20lot%20like%20super-expanded%20autocorrect%3F%20And%20I%20think%20the%20answer%20is%20quite%20a%20lot.%20So%20this%20is%20potentially%20a%20really%20big%20thing%2C%20and%20it%20could%20displace%20a%20lot%20of%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20does%20%26quot%3Ba%20really%20big%20thing%26quot%3B%20translate%20into%20a%20measurable%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%3F%20Krugman%20said%20it's%20still%20hard%20to%20gauge%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-is-changing-everything-2019-7%5C%22%3Eimpact%20of%20technological%20innovation%20like%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20way%20we%20%26quot%3Bmeasure%20technology%20is%20godawful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrugman%20explained%20that%20economists%20usually%20add%20up%20tangible%20metrics%20like%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20stock%20of%20capital%20to%20economic%20growth%26quot%3B%20and%20chalk%20up%20what%20can't%20be%20measured%20to%20technological%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20because%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20else%20to%20measure%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20he%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-saw-productivity-increase-throughout-the-pandemic-but-employee-burnout-is-an-ongoing-concern-2021-10%5C%22%3Ecountry's%20productivity%20accelerated%20%3C%2Fa%3Eat%20a%20rate%20of%201%25%20a%20year%20between%20the%20mid-90s%20and%20early%202000s%2C%20which%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20companies%20finally%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20leverage%20information%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20growth%2C%20though%2C%20also%20just%20came%20from%20more%20commonplace%20things%20like%20companies%20figuring%20out%20how%20to%20use%20barcodes%20to%20manage%20their%20inventories%2C%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20basically%20technology%20is%20the%20measure%20of%20what%20you%20can't%20explain%20otherwise%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20said.%20What%20it%20will%20mean%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%2C%20only%20time%20will%20tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20AI%20already%20replacing%20part%20of%20your%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Or%20are%20you%20looking%20to%20use%20it%20to%20replace%20employees%3F%20It's%20still%20early%20days%2C%20but%20we%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you%20if%20you're%20using%20AI%20in%20your%20day-to-day%20work.%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20lvaranasi%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-says-ai-will-mean-job-losses-no-solution-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691777244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d66568f3f87e001951d9c