ated%20on%20extra-large%20TVs%20that%20are%2075%20inches%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20use%2065%20inches%20as%20their%20flagship%20size%20to%20show%20off%20their%20best%20TV%20models%2C%20and%20we%20think%20this%20size%20offers%20a%20great%20balance%20between%20big-screen%20immersion%20and%20value%2C%20without%20getting%20too%20big%20for%20most%20living%20rooms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20smart%20TV%20interfaces%20does%20each%20brand%20use%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20any%20new%20TV%20you%20buy%20in%202023%20will%20be%20a%20smart%20TV%20with%20built-in%20support%20for%20accessing%20various%20streaming%20services.%20However%2C%20different%20brands%20use%20different%20smart%20TV%20operating%20systems%20(OS).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20breakdown%20of%20popular%20smart%20TV%20platforms%20and%20the%20brands%20that%20use%20them%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAndroid%20TV%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOlder%20models%20from%20Sony%2C%20TCL%2C%20and%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFire%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Amazon%2C%20Toshiba%2C%20Insignia%2C%20Pioneer%2C%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoogle%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Sony%2C%20TCL%2C%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoku%20TV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Roku%2C%20TCL%2C%20Hisense%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmartCast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Vizio%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETizen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Samsung%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EwebOS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20LG%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20slight%20differences%20in%20the%20selection%20of%20apps%20across%20each%20service%2C%20but%20every%20major%20smart%20TV%20platform%20offers%20access%20to%20all%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20streaming%20services.%20They%20all%20deliver%20similar%20features%20as%20well%2C%20but%20the%20style%20of%20navigation%2C%20personalization%20options%2C%20and%20extra%20perks%20all%20vary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20we%20like%20Roku's%20interface%20the%20best%20since%20it's%20the%20most%20straightforward%20and%20reliable%20of%20the%20bunch.%20However%2C%20its%20design%20is%20a%20little%20outdated%20compared%20to%20other%20platforms%20that%20offer%20a%20more%20slick%2C%20content-focused%20style.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20smart%20TV%20OS%20is%20best%20for%20your%20needs%20really%20comes%20down%20to%20personal%20preference%20and%20whether%20you're%20already%20plugged%20into%20a%20smart%20home%20ecosystem.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20Google%20TV%20or%20Fire%20TV%20will%20pair%20more%20seamlessly%20with%20existing%20Google%20or%20Amazon%20accounts%20and%20devices%20you%20might%20already%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20like%20the%20interface%20that%20comes%20built%20into%20your%20TV%2C%20we%20recommend%20checking%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-streaming-box-stick%5C%22%3Ebest%20streaming%20devices%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20choose%20a%20standalone%20streaming%20device%20with%20whatever%20OS%20you%20prefer.%20Standalone%20streaming%20players%20also%20tend%20to%20offer%20snappier%20performance%20than%20built-in%20smart%20TV%20interfaces.%20Roku%20and%20Fire%20TV%20devices%20are%20frequently%20on%20sale%20for%20as%20little%20as%20%2420.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20OLED%2C%20QLED%2C%20and%20LED%20TVs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20buy%20a%20TV%20in%202023%2C%20chances%20are%20it%20will%20be%20branded%20as%20one%20of%20four%20primary%20display%20types%3A%20%3Cstrong%3EOLED%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EQD-OLED%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EQLED%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20or%20%3Cstrong%3ELED%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Though%20performance%20varies%20depending%20on%20which%20specific%20model%20you%20buy%2C%20each%20technology%20has%20its%20own%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20that%20could%20make%20it%20better%20suited%20for%20different%20kinds%20of%20viewers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20rundown%20of%20pros%20and%20cons%20for%20each%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Ch3%3EOLED%20TVs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20OLED%20(organic%20light-emitting%20diode)%20TV%20uses%20self-illuminating%20pixel%20technology%20to%20display%20its%20images%20without%20the%20need%20for%20a%20backlight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20it's%20best%20for%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20OLED%20TVs%20are%20best%20for%20people%20who%20want%20high-end%20picture%20performance%20in%20a%20space%20that%20doesn't%20let%20in%20a%20ton%20of%20ambient%20light.%20Though%20they%20still%20look%20good%20in%20most%20living%20rooms%2C%20they%20can%20be%20too%20dim%20for%20areas%20filled%20with%20direct%20sunlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInfinite%20contrast%20ratio%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrue%20black%20levels%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWide%20viewing%20angles%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExpanded%20color%20gamut%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOverall%20performance%20is%20similar%20across%20different%20models%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPeak%20brightness%20is%20typically%20dimmer%20than%20top%20QD-OLED%20or%20QLED%20TVs*%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EColor%20volume%20can't%20match%20the%20best%20TVs%20with%20quantum%20dots%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20risk%20of%20burn-in%20in%20extreme%20cases%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELimited%20sizes%20and%20budget-tiers%20to%20choose%20from%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E*LG's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-61243-20%26h%3D49b392501f0104c71d7fd59aa9a42d7690db9643df29b317538534d06f60b771%26postID%3D64d3f44b15e1ae2efa1b013c%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FLG-65-Inch-Processor-AI-Powered-OLED65G3PUA%252Fdp%252FB0BVWZJ2YV%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EG3%20OLED%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20uses%20Micro%20Lens%20Array%20(MLA)%20technology%2C%20which%20enables%20it%20to%20match%20the%20peak%20brightness%20of%20top%20QD-OLED%20TVs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Ch3%3EQD-OLED%20TVs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20QD-OLED%20TV%20is%20a%20type%20of%20OLED%20TV%20that%20adds%20a%20filter%20of%20quantum%20dots%20in%20its%20panel%20to%20enable%20better%20color%20and%20brightness%20performance%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20it's%20best%20for%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20QD-OLED%20TVs%20are%20great%20for%20people%20who%20want%20the%20absolute%20best%20picture%20quality.%20Since%20they're%20brighter%20than%20regular%20OLED%20models%2C%20QD-OLED%20TVs%20are%20suited%20for%20both%20home%20theaters%20and%20average%20living%20rooms%20alike%2C%20and%20they%20deliver%20a%20bit%20more%20HDR%20punch%20in%20highlights.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInfinite%20contrast%20ratio%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrue%20black%20levels%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWide%20viewing%20angles%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExpanded%20color%20gamut%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrighter%20than%20a%20regular%20OLED%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBetter%20color%20volume%20than%20a%20standard%20OLED%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPeak%20brightness%20still%20can't%20match%20top%20QLED%20TVs%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20risk%20of%20burn-in%20in%20extreme%20cases%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELimited%20sizes%20and%20budget-tiers%20to%20choose%20from%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Caside%3E%3Ch3%3EQLED%20TVs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20QLED%20is%20a%20TV%20that%20uses%20an%20LCD%20(liquid%20crystal%20display)%20panel%20with%20an%20LED%20(light%20emitting%20diode)%20or%20Mini%20LED%20backlight%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20filter%20of%20quantum%20dots.%20QLED%20TVs%20may%20or%20may%20not%20include%20local%20dimming%2C%20which%20enables%20contrast%20control%20over%20specific%20LEDs%20on%20the%20screen.%20To%20get%20the%20best%20performance%20on%20a%20QLED%20TV%2C%20you%20should%20look%20for%20models%20with%20local%20dimming%20and%20a%20Mini%20LED%20backlight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20it's%20best%20for%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20QLED%20TVs%20are%20good%20for%20people%20who%20favor%20high%20brightness%20to%20get%20the%20best%20performance%20in%20rooms%20that%20let%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20outside%20light.%20High-end%20models%20can%20also%20deliver%20excellent%20overall%20picture%20performance%20with%20vibrant%20HDR%20highlights%2C%20but%20we%20still%20prefer%20OLED%20technology%20for%20the%20best%20quality%20in%20a%20home%20theater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETop%20models%20have%20industry-leading%20brightness%20and%20color%20volume%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EModels%20with%20local%20dimming%20and%20Mini%20LEDs%20can%20provide%20great%20contrast%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENo%20risk%20of%20burn-in%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELots%20of%20sizes%20and%20budget-tiers%20to%20choose%20from%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEven%20top%20Mini%20LED%20models%20can't%20match%20the%20contrast%20of%20an%20OLED%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBlack%20levels%20are%20lacking%20on%20models%20without%20local%20dimming%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EViewing%20angles%20are%20typically%20mediocre%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPerformance%20varies%20a%20lot%20across%20different%20models%20and%20budget-tiers%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Caside%3E%3Ch3%3ELED%20TVs%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20LED%20TV%20uses%20LCD%20panel%20technology%20with%20an%20LED%20or%20Mini%20LED%20backlight.%20Backlights%20can%20either%20be%20direct%20or%20edge-lit.%20The%20main%20difference%20between%20an%20LED%20and%20QLED%20TV%2C%20is%20that%20LED%20TVs%20don't%20use%20quantum%20dots.%20Most%20TVs%20branded%20as%20LED%20are%20budget-focused%20models%20without%20local%20dimming%20or%20wide%20color%20support%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20exceptions*.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20it's%20best%20for%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20LED%20TVs%20are%20best%20suited%20for%20budget%20shoppers.%20Most%20of%20these%20displays%20only%20offer%20basic%20image%20quality%20and%20lack%20the%20color%20and%20contrast%20performance%20you'd%20get%20on%20a%20QLED%20or%20OLED.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENo%20risk%20of%20burn-in%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELots%20of%20sizes%20and%20affordable%20options%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETypically%20lack%20wide%20color%20support%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EContrast%20is%20mediocre%20without%20local%20dimming%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEdge-lit%20backlights%20can%20lead%20to%20uneven%20black%20levels%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EViewing%20angles%20are%20usually%20mediocre%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E*Sony%20still%20sells%20midrange%20and%20high-end%20TVs%20branded%20as%20just%20%26quot%3BLED%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3BQLED.%26quot%3B%20Some%20top%20Sony%20LED%20TVs%20include%20local%20dimming%2C%20Mini%20LEDs%2C%20and%20wide%20color%20support%2C%20which%20puts%20them%20in%20the%20same%20class%20as%20top%20QLEDs%20from%20other%20brands.%20But%20because%20Sony%20doesn't%20use%20%26quot%3Bquantum%20dot%26quot%3B%20terminology%20for%20its%20wide%20color%20tech%20it%20doesn't%20brand%20these%20TVs%20as%20QLED.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EShould%20I%20be%20worried%20about%20burn-in%20on%20my%20TV%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20leave%20a%20static%20image%20on%20your%20TV%20for%20too%20long%2C%20some%20displays%20are%20susceptible%20to%20an%20issue%20called%20burn-in.%20When%20burn-in%20occurs%2C%20a%20faint%20outline%20of%20an%20image%20gets%20permanently%20stuck%20on%20your%20display.%20Thankfully%2C%20burn-in%20is%20rare%20on%20modern%20TVs%20so%20most%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20it.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20some%20considerations%20you%20should%20be%20aware%20of.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20and%20foremost%2C%20OLED%20is%20the%20only%20current%20TV%20technology%20that%20is%20prone%20to%20burn-in.%20Though%20LCD-based%20TVs%2C%20like%20QLED%20and%20LED%2C%20are%20not%20100%25%20immune%20to%20burn-in%2C%20cases%20are%20so%20rare%20that%20they're%20not%20considered%20to%20be%20at%20risk%20in%20the%20same%20way%20an%20OLED%20TV%20is.%20But%20while%20OLED%20shoppers%20should%20be%20mindful%20of%20this%20risk%2C%20all%20OLED%20TVs%20have%20built-in%20features%20designed%20to%20prevent%20burn-in%2C%20including%20pixel-shift%20modes%20and%20pixel-refreshers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWebsites%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rtings.com%2Ftv%2Ftests%2Flongevity-burn-in-test-updates-and-results%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERtings%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20done%20long-term%20burn-in%20tests%20with%20various%20OLED%20models.%20Though%20their%20results%20do%20prove%20that%20burn-in%20can%20happen%20on%20modern%20OLED%20TVs%2C%20their%20tests%20reveal%20that%20it's%20not%20really%20an%20issue%20for%20people%20with%20regular%20viewing%20habits.%20Burn-in%20only%20occurs%20in%20extreme%20situations%2C%20like%20if%20you%20just%20watch%20the%20same%20cable%20channel%20with%20the%20same%20logo%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20screen%20all%20day%20long.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20personally%20owned%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhome-theater-ideas-my-entertainment-setup%5C%22%3ELG%20CX%20OLED%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20two%20years.%20I%20stream%20various%20services%2C%20watch%20cable%20TV%2C%20and%20play%20video%20games%20(which%20have%20plenty%20of%20static%20elements)%20regularly%2C%20and%20the%20TV%20shows%20no%20signs%20of%20burn-in.%20Unless%20you're%20someone%20who%20plans%20to%20stay%20tuned%20to%20the%20same%20cable%20news%20channel%2024%2F7%2C%20we%20don't%20think%20burn-in%20should%20be%20a%20primary%20factor%20when%20deciding%20between%20an%20OLED%20TV%20or%20another%20display%20type