C%2022%20years%20later%2C%20he%20resumes%20his%20role%20in%20the%20sequel.%20As%20the%20film%20releases%20today%2C%20Utkarsh%20talks%20about%20working%20with%20his%20father%2C%20Sunny%20Deol%20and%20his%20aspirations%20as%20an%20actor.%20Read%20on..%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Ankita%20Kanabar%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Futkarsh-sharma-the-biggest-of-the-stars-can-give-a-big-hit-and-might-have-to-wait-for-10-years-for-another-theres-so-much-uncertainty%2Farticleshow%2F102653147.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20In%20No-Trust%20Debate%2C%20Signs%20That%20BJP%20Is%20Rattled%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20fundamental%20question%20that%20one%20may%20ask%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20recent%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20parliament%20is%2C%20why%20our%20Constitution%20makers%20chose%20a%20parliamentary%20form%20of%20democracy%20for%20India.%20The%20simple%20answer%20is%20that%20it%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20make%20the%20executive%20accountable%20to%20the%20people%20through%20parliament%2C%20which%20reflects%20the%20sovereign%20will%20of%20the%20people.%20It%20is%20why%20the%20opposition%20succeeded%20in%20forcing%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20speak%20on%20Manipur%2C%20where%20a%20civil%20war-like%20situation%20has%20prevailed%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%20The%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20known%20for%20speaking%20on%20sundry%20issues%2C%20has%20been%20quiet%20on%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20the%20opposition%20demanded%20that%20Manipur%20be%20discussed%20and%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20make%20a%20statement.%20The%20government%20was%20ready%20to%20discuss%20Manipur%20under%20Rule%20176%20for%20a%20short%20duration%20discussion%20but%20the%20opposition%20insisted%20Manipur%20was%20too%20big%2C%20that%20all%20business%20should%20be%20suspended%20for%20a%20discussion%20under%20Rule%20267%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20should%20speak%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20conflict%20between%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20government%2C%20several%20days%20of%20parliament%20were%20washed%20out.%20When%20the%20opposition%20realised%20the%20government%20would%20not%20agree%20to%20their%20demand%2C%20it%20chose%20the%20path%20of%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20which%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20mandatorily%2C%20has%20to%20speak%20in%20the%20end.%20Indeed%2C%20that%20is%20what%20happened.%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20to%20reply%20and%20he%20did%20talk%20about%20Manipur.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20opposition%20could%20claim%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20the%20opposition%20actually%20gained%20from%20the%20entire%20exercise%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20debate.%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20seized%20the%20opportunity%20to%20turn%20the%20tables%20on%20the%20opposition%2C%20called%20it%20names%2C%20tried%20to%20depict%20the%20parties%20as%20good-for-nothing%20and%20boasted%20that%20his%20third%20consecutive%20term%20is%20assured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%2C%20however%2C%20to%20realise%20that%20it%20is%20no%20mean%20feat%20for%20the%20opposition%20to%20force%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20who%20was%20silent%20on%20Manipur%2C%20to%20speak%20and%20make%20him%20accountable%20to%20the%20people%20of%20India.%20Let%20us%20not%20forget%20that%20this%20happened%20at%20a%20time%20when%20serious%20questions%20are%20being%20raised%20by%20critics%20and%20well-wishers%20who%20claim%20India's%20democracy%20is%20no%20longer%20as%20robust%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20and%20that%20it%20has%20turned%20into%20an%20'electoral%20autocracy'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20well%20be%20argued%20that%20the%20opposition%20did%20not%20do%20its%20homework%20and%20failed%20to%20put%20the%20government%20on%20the%20mat.%20Due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20coordination%20between%20the%20different%20constituents%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20the%20opposition's%20charge%20was%20disorganised%20and%20could%20not%20effectively%20expose%20the%20mishandling%20of%20both%20the%20centre%20and%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%2C%20however%2C%20been%20ignored%20is%20that%20if%20the%20opposition%20was%20so%20feeble%20and%20uninspiring%20-%20as%20projected%20by%20a%20section%20of%20the%20TV%20media%20-%20then%20why%20did%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20have%20to%20spend%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20his%20speech%20ridiculing%20the%20opposition%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20remember%20a%20more%20uninspiring%20speech%20by%20any%20Prime%20Minister%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20house.%20PM%20Modi%20looked%20tired%20and%20his%20speech%20was%20laboured%2C%20until%20the%20opposition%20walked%20out%20in%20protest.%20After%20the%20opposition's%20walkout%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20suddenly%20regained%20his%20mojo%2C%20but%20by%20then%20it%20was%20too%20late.%20The%20only%20explanation%20for%20spending%20so%20much%20time%20on%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20opposition%20would%20be%20that%20he%20is%20no%20longer%20confident%20about%20the%202024%20general%20elections%2C%20and%20the%20sudden%20grouping%20of%2026%20political%20parties%20has%20taken%20him%20by%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20not%20required%20to%20mention%20the%20Bengaluru%20meet%20of%20the%20opposition%20where%20the%20name%20INDIA%20was%20chosen%20for%20the%20alliance.%20He%20said%20the%20last%20rites%20of%20the%20UPA%20were%20performed%20to%20hoodwink%20the%20people%20of%20India.%20In%20his%20opinion%2C%20it%20is%20an%20effort%20to%20hide%20their%20sins%20and%20deceive%20people%20to%20capture%20power.%20He%20warned%20that%20people%20should%20not%20forget%20that%20these%20are%20the%20people%20who%20had%20looted%20the%20country%20in%20the%20past.%20He%20boasted%20that%20his%20government%20would%20again%20win%20a%20majority%20and%20that%20he%20is%20destined%20to%20make%20India%20the%20third%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20-%20like%2C%20in%209%20years%2C%20he%20made%20India%20not%20only%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy%20but%20also%20fifth%20largest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20how%20PM%20Modi%20has%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20the%202024%20national%20election.%20He%20used%20parliament%20to%20build%20a%20narrative%20for%20the%20election.%20It%20had%20three%20major%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20aware%20that%20the%20Congress%2C%20with%2012%20crore%20votes%20and%20a%2019%25%20vote%20share%20across%20the%20country%2C%20is%20the%20only%20party%20with%20an%20all-India%20footprint%20and%20the%20potential%20to%20emerge%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20the%20BJP%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Ten%20years%20is%20a%20long%20enough%20for%20anti-incumbency%20to%20build%20against%20any%20government.%20So%2C%20to%20counter%20that%2C%20it%20is%20important%20for%20him%20to%20discredit%20the%20Congress%20and%20kill%20any%20possibility%20of%20it%20posing%20a%20serious%20challenge%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20north%20and%20western%20India%20where%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20are%20direct%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%2C%20historically%2C%20whenever%20a%20fragmented%20opposition%20has%20come%20together%2C%20it%20has%20created%20problems%20for%20the%20ruling%20party.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20the%20Congress%20suffered%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20knows%20that%20with%2037%25%20votes%2C%20it%20is%20vulnerable%20too.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20spent%20a%20considerable%20time%20mocking%20INDIA%20and%20reminding%20people%20that%20the%20name%20INDIA%2C%20despite%20sounding%20pious%2C%20is%20an%20opportunist%20alliance%20of%20corrupt%20parties%20and%20leaders%20who%20have%20come%20together%20to%20fulfil%20their%20vested%20interest.%20Their%20slogan%20-%20%26quot%3Bto%20save%20democracy%2C%20save%20the%20Constitution%20and%20save%20the%20Idea%20of%20India%26quot%3B%20-%20was%20merely%20a%20smokescreen%20to%20grab%20power%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%2C%20if%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20invested%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20time%20on%20painting%20a%20negative%20image%20of%20the%20opposition%2C%20then%20he%20also%20projected%20himself%20as%20someone%20who%20is%20development-oriented%20and%20the%20only%20one%20to%20Make%20India%20Great%20Again.%20He%20talked%20about%20how%2C%20during%20his%20tenure%2C%20India's%20stature%20had%20skyrocketed%20globally.%20India%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20pushover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20in%20parliament%20has%20also%20ensured%20that%20the%20opposition%2C%20unlike%20in%202019%2C%20is%20determined%20and%20the%20fight%20for%202024%20will%20not%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi's%20fierce%20criticism%20is%20a%20warning.%20His%20attack%20on%20nationalism%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20convey%20to%20the%20people%20that%20the%20government's%20claims%20of%20being%20the%20epitome%20of%20nationalism%20are%20hollow%2C%20a%20vote-grabbing%20tactic%2C%20and%20that%20their%20commitment%20to%20%26quot%3BBharat%20Mata%26quot%3B%20is%20devoid%20of%20any%20spiritual%20awakening.%20It%20is%20just%20an%20excuse%20to%20use%20innocent%20citizens%20for%20electoral%20gains.%20It%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20watch%20what%20shape%20this%20war%20takes%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%20What%20is%20certain%20is%20that%20this%20time%2C%20the%20election%20will%20have%20all%20the%20trappings%20of%20a%20blockbuster%20movie.%20What%20we%20saw%20in%20parliament%20was%20only%20the%20teaser.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Ashutosh%20is%20author%20of%20'Hindu%20Rashtra'%20and%20Editor%2C%20satyahindi.com.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691760780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F4jsi3eng_pm-modi-ani-650_650x400_10_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-pms-no-trust-speech-glimpses-of-2024-strategy-4290360%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20this%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20the%20opposition%20demanded%20that%20Manipur%20be%20discussed%20and%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20make%20a%20statement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-pms-no-trust-speech-glimpses-of-2024-strategy-4290360%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-pms-no-trust-speech-glimpses-of-2024-strategy-4290360%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-pms-no-trust-speech-glimpses-of-2024-strategy-4290360%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Govt%20Unveils%20Controversial%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20'Sedition'%20Law%20to%20Change%20But%20in%20Name%20Only%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09222428%2FAmit-Anil-Chandra-Shah-in-Lok-Sabha.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20Friday%20(August%2011)%20announced%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20decided%20to%20%E2%80%9Crepeal%E2%80%9D%20the%20sedition%20law%2C%20as%20he%20introduced%20three%20new%20Bills%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20a%20move%20to%20reform%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20and%20shed%20its%20colonial%20legacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20new%20bills%20include%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%3B%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201898%3B%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20British%20laws%20were%20made%20to%20strengthen%20and%20protect%20the%20British%20government%20and%20the%20aim%20was%20to%20punish%20and%20not%20bring%20justice.%20The%20spirit%20of%20three%20new%20laws%20that%20we%20are%20bringing%20will%20not%20be%20to%20punish%20but%20to%20give%20justice%20to%20every%20citizen%20and%20to%20prevent%20further%20crimes%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20gave%20a%20brief%20introduction%20of%20the%20three%20new%20Bills%20and%20said%20that%20they%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20and%20will%20be%20presented%20to%20the%20parliament%20thereafter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proposed%20legislation%20brings%20important%20changes%2C%20by%20criminalising%20mob%20lynching%20and%20marrying%20or%20having%20sexual%20relations%20with%20a%20woman%20by%20deception.%20It%20also%20provides%20for%20compulsory%20video%20recording%20of%20the%20statements%20by%20victims%20of%20sexual%20crimes%2C%20imposing%20time%20limits%20for%20filing%20chargesheets%20and%20completion%20of%20trials%2C%20as%20well%20as%20conducting%20trials%20for%20criminals%20who%20are%20absconding%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESedition%20replaced%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98draconian%E2%80%99%20provision%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20important%20change%2C%20however%2C%20as%20hailed%20by%20Shah%2C%20has%20been%20to%20drop%20the%20provision%20of%20sedition%20under%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSedition%20(law)%20was%20brought%20(by%20the%20British)%20to%20save%20their%20rule.%20We%20have%20taken%20the%20historic%20decision%20to%20repeal%20sedition%20completely.%20This%20is%20a%20democracy%2C%20everyone%20has%20the%20right%20to%20speak%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20a%20look%20at%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fthe-bharatiya-nyaya-sanhita-2023-485731.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Section%20150%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%202023%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eshows%20that%20while%20the%20word%20sedition%20may%20have%20been%20removed%2C%20the%20law%20remains%20and%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20has%20been%20made%20more%20draconian%20by%20making%20it%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20seven%20years%20imprisonment%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%20150%20details%20Acts%20endangering%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%2C%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhoever%2C%20purposely%20or%20knowingly%2C%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20by%20electronic%20communication%20or%20by%20use%20of%20financial%20mean%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%2C%20secession%20or%20armed%20rebellion%20or%20subversive%20activities%2C%20or%20encourages%20feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%20or%20endangers%20sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%3B%20or%20indulges%20in%20or%20commits%20any%20such%20act%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20seven%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20explanation%20of%20the%20section%20states%20the%20following%3A%20%E2%80%9CComments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20measures%2C%20or%20administrative%20or%20other%20action%20of%20the%20Government%20with%20a%20view%20to%20obtain%20their%20alteration%20by%20lawful%20means%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20the%20activities%20referred%20to%20in%20this%20section.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20the%20Sedition%20law%20(Under%20124A%20IPC)%20had%20stated%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhoever%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20brings%20or%20attempts%20to%20bring%20into%20hatred%20or%20contempt%2C%20or%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%20disaffection%20towards%2C%20the%20Government%20established%20by%20law%20in%203%5BIndia%5D%2C%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%205%5Bimprisonment%20for%20life%5D%2C%20to%20which%20fine%20may%20be%20added%2C%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20three%20years%2C%20to%20which%20fine%20may%20be%20added%2C%20or%20with%20fine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20explanation%2C%20the%20law%20defined%20the%20expression%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%E2%80%9D%20as%20including%20disloyalty%20and%20all%20feelings%20of%20enmity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Section%20also%20explained%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccomments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20measures%20of%20the%20Government%20with%20a%20view%20to%20obtain%20their%20alteration%20by%20lawful%20means%2C%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%2C%20do%20not%20constitute%20an%20offence%20under%20this%20section.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20further%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccomments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20administrative%20or%20other%20action%20of%20the%20Government%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%2C%20do%20not%20constitute%20an%20offence%20under%20this%20section.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EAnas%20Tanwir%2C%20advocate%20on%20record%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20founder%20of%20Indian%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union%20said%20that%20the%20explanation%20under%20Section%20150%20of%20the%20new%20law%20is%20%E2%80%9Cincomplete%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20it%20removed%20sedition%2C%20it%20makes%20a%20far%20more%20draconian%20provision.%20The%20explanation%20of%20the%20law%20appears%20incomplete.%20And%20it%20brings%20into%20its%20purview%20the%20potential%20to%20criminalise%20protest%20against%20any%20law%20or%20any%20action%20that%20the%20govt%20does%20not%20deem%20fit%20by%20using%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activity%E2%80%99%20which%20is%20a%20very%20vague%20term%20and%20can%20include%20anything%2C%20even%20a%20protest%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20offences%20and%20stricter%20punishments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20said%20that%20in%20recent%20years%20there%20has%20been%20talk%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20law%20for%20mob%20lynching%20which%20has%20been%20addressed%20in%20the%20new%20legislation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20has%20been%20said%20about%20mob%20lynching%20in%20the%20last%20seven%20years.%20Now%20mob%20lynching%20will%20have%20a%20punishment%20of%20seven%20years%20imprisonment%20or%20for%20life%20or%20death%20penalty%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20added%20that%20in%20cases%20of%20gang%20rape%2C%20punishment%20has%20been%20increased%20and%20may%20now%20include%2020-year%20imprisonment%20as%20well%20as%20imprisonment%20for%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20cases%20involving%20girls%20less%20than%2018%20years%20old%2C%20provision%20of%20capital%20punishment%20has%20been%20made%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReferring%20to%20absconding%20criminals%20like%20Dawood%20Ibrahim%2C%20Shah%20said%20provisions%20have%20been%20made%20to%20hold%20trials%20in%20absentia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20cases%2C%20people%20like%20Dawood%20Ibrahim%20would%20commit%20crimes%20and%20run%20away.%20Now%20trials%20will%20take%20place%20despite%20their%20absence.%20If%20they%20have%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%20judgment%2C%20then%20they%20have%20to%20come%20to%20India%20and%20then%20appeal%20to%20Indian%20courts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReferring%20to%20cases%20of%20criminals%20who%20have%20political%20clout%20and%20remission%20of%20their%20sentences%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20they%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20not%20be%20let%20go%E2%80%9D%20as%20was%20seen%20in%20Bihar%20recently%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhy-did-the-bihar-govt-change-remission-rules-to-aid-the-release-of-convicted-killer-anand-mohan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealluding%20to%20the%20release%20of%20Anand%20Mohan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20account%20of%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20heft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sentence%20can%20be%20remitted%20from%20death%20to%20life%20imprisonment%2C%20life%20imprisonment%20to%20seven%20years%2C%20and%20seven%20years%20to%20three%20years.%20Anyone%20who%20has%20political%20connections%20will%20not%20be%20let%20go%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20a%20separate%20category%20of%20crime%20has%20been%20brought%20for%20marrying%20or%20having%20sexual%20relations%20with%20a%20woman%20by%20deception%20or%20wrong%20credentials%2C%20as%20well%20as%20snatching%20which%20was%20not%20defined%20earlier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20laws%20will%20also%20make%20it%20compulsory%20for%20the%20police%20to%20record%20video%20statements%20of%20a%20survivor%20of%20sexual%20abuse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20to%20streamline%20the%20trial%20and%20chargesheeting%20process%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20a%20time%20limit%20of%2090%20days%20will%20be%20imposed%20within%20which%20a%20chargesheet%20has%20to%20be%20filed.%20This%20deadline%20can%20be%20extended%20by%20another%2090%20days%20by%20courts%20but%20after%20180%20days%20the%20case%20will%20have%20to%20go%20to%20trial.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20arguments%20conclude%2C%20judgments%20have%20to%20be%20given%20by%20courts%20within%2030%20days.%20Judgments%20will%20also%20have%20to%20be%20uploaded%20within%20seven%20days%20so%20an%20appeal%20can%20be%20filed%20if%20needed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOrganised%20crime%20has%20also%20been%20made%20a%20punishable%20offence%20and%20community%20service%20has%20been%20introduced%20for%20the%20first%20time%20for%20certain%20crimes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20to%20bring%20accountability%20to%20the%20police%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20force%20will%20have%20to%20provide%20documentary%20and%20digital%20evidence%20if%20a%20person%20has%20been%20arrested.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COften%20we%20see%20that%20the%20police%20after%20arresting%20a%20person%20don%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20for%20up%20to%204%20days.%20Now%20they%20will%20have%20to%20give%20physical%20and%20digital%20notification%20to%20the%20relatives%20of%20the%20accused%20that%20their%20kin%20has%20been%20taken%20into%20custody.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20changes%20have%20been%20brought%20in%20to%20digitise%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system.%20Forensic%20evidence%20has%20been%20mandatory%20for%20crimes%20punishable%20with%207%20years%20and%20above.%20If%20a%20case%20that%20has%20gone%20on%20for%20over%207%20years%20has%20to%20be%20withdrawn%2C%20then%20it%20has%20to%20take%20the%20victim%E2%80%99s%20consent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20will%20protect%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKey%20features%20of%20new%20Bills%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20said%20that%20the%20three%20new%20Bills%20will%20bring%20important%20changes%20to%20make%20them%20relevant%20to%20Indian%20society%20and%20drop%20references%20to%20colonial%20rule.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20will%20replace%20CrPC%20will%20have%20533%20provisions.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20changed%20160%20provisions%2C%20added%209%20new%20provisions%20and%209%20provisions%20have%20been%20removed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20IPC%20will%20have%20511%20provisions%20against%20the%20356%20in%20the%20earlier%20law.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20changes%20in%20175%20provisions%2C%208%20new%20provisions%20have%20been%20added%20and%2022%20have%20been%20removed%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20will%20have%20170%20provisions%20instead%20of%20the%20166%20earlier.%20%E2%80%9C23%20provisions%20have%20been%20changed%2C%20one%20has%20been%20added%20and%20five%20removed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Shah%2C%20these%20three%20laws%20were%20full%20of%20references%20to%20colonialism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20existing%20laws%20have%20references%20to%20the%20parliament%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20provincial%20act%2C%20notification%20by%20the%20Crown%2C%20London%20Gazette%2C%20jury%20and%20Barrister(which%20is%20not%20there%20in%20our%20country)%2C%20Lahore%20government%2C%20Commonwealth%2C%20Privy%20Council%2C%20British%20Crown%2C%20Court%20of%20Justice%20in%20England%2C%20Her%20Majesty%20dominions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20total%20of%20475%20references%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egulaami%20ki%20nishani%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(signs%20of%20slavery)%20have%20been%20removed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EManner%20of%20introduction%20%E2%80%98unfair%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20new%20legislations%20will%20overhaul%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20lawyers%20said%20that%20it%20could%20bring%20operational%20difficulties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcerns%20were%20also%20raised%20that%20the%20Bills%20were%20introduced%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20monsoon%20session%20and%20listed%20moments%20before%20their%20introduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20should%20have%20been%20a%20wider%20consultation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tanwir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIntroduction%20on%20the%20last%20day%20is%20unfair%20but%20the%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20may%20consider%20amending%20rather%20than%20bringing%20new%20laws%20as%20there%20may%20be%20difficulties%20in%20interpreting%20provisions%2C%20bringing%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20to%20a%20grinding%20halt.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20he%20added%20that%20the%20move%20to%20bring%20in%20changes%20like%20defining%20mob%20lynching%20is%20welcome.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20welcome%20move%20because%20earlier%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20also%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20come%20up%20with%20data%20and%20there%20was%20never%20any%20data%20as%20it%20%5Bmob%20lynching%5D%C2%A0%20was%20not%20defined.%20Now%20at%20least%20there%20is%20the%20provision%20to%20have%20that%20data%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20also%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20lack%20of%20consultation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang