n%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20alleged%20that%2C%20after%20the%20firm%20advised%20the%20government%20on%20tougher%20tax%20laws%2C%20it%20then%20leaked%20the%20design%20of%20those%20laws%20to%20its%20clients%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20whom%20would%20be%20targeted%20by%20the%20proposed%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20these%20kinds%20of%20questions%20have%20been%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20recent%20examples%20of%20this%20issue%20being%20explored%20include%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmc.gov.au%2Fpublications%2Findependent-review-australian-public-service%5C%22%3EThodey%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Australian%20Public%20Service%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anao.gov.au%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FANAO_Report_2017-2018_19.pdf%5C%22%3E2017%20Australian%20National%20Audit%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20audit%20of%20Commonwealth%20departments%E2%80%99%20use%20of%20consultants%20and%20contractors%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.audit.vic.gov.au%2Freport%2Fmanaging-consultants-and-contractors%3Fsection%3D%5C%22%3E2014%20audit%20by%20the%20Victorian%20Auditor-General%E2%80%99s%20Office.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20could%20be%20forgiven%20for%20dismissing%20this%20matter%20as%20an%20insider%20issue%20of%20public%20administration%20best%20left%20to%20the%20boffins%20to%20thrash%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20PwC%20scandal%20illustrates%2C%20the%20excessive%20use%20of%20consultants%20has%20very%20real%20implications%20for%20democratic%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20many%20experts%20argue%20the%20influx%20of%20consultants%20represents%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FShadow-Government-Governments-Multi-Billion-Dollar-Decision-Making%2Fdp%2F0394492447%5C%22%3Eshadow%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20plundering%20the%20public%20sector.%20Some%20go%20so%20far%20as%20to%20say%20that%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbristoluniversitypressdigital.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fpp%2F35%2F3%2Farticle-p479.xml%5C%22%3Erepresents%20private%20control%20over%20public%20policy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20therefore%20timely%20to%20consider%20why%20governments%20use%20consultants%20so%20much%2C%20why%20that%20might%20be%20a%20problem%2C%20and%20what%20we%20can%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consulting%20industry%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%20father%20of%20so-called%20%E2%80%98scientific%20management%E2%80%99%2C%20Frederick%20Winslow%20Taylor%2C%20and%20his%20cohort%20of%20%E2%80%98efficiency%20engineers%2C%20which%20included%20such%20business%20luminaries%20as%20Henry%20Gantt%2C%20Lillian%20and%20Frank%20Gilbreth%2C%20and%20Harrington%20Emerson.%20This%20group%20could%20be%20considered%20the%20first%20management%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20involved%20in%20advising%20the%20United%20States%E2%80%99%20government%20on%20matters%20of%20efficiency%2C%20administration%2C%20or%20organisational%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Hoover%20Commission%20in%201947%20hired%20two%20consulting%20firms%20to%20provide%20advice%20on%20reforms%20to%20public%20administration.%20Likewise%2C%20political%20scientist%20Denis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.gale.com%2Fapps%2Fdoc%2FA21249108%2FAONE%3Fu%3Dusyd%26sid%3DgoogleScholar%26xid%3D717334af%5C%22%3ESaint-Martin%20has%20described%20the%201960%20Canadian%20Glassco%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20Government%20Reorganisation%20as%20%E2%80%98by%20far%20the%20most%20impressive%20demonstration%20of%20the%20influence%20of%20consultants%20in%20government%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20received%20a%20massive%20%E2%80%98shot%20in%20the%20arm%E2%80%99%20through%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20bundle%20of%20reforms%20collectively%20known%20as%20the%20new%20public%20management.%20This%20introduced%20into%20government%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%98Hands%20on%E2%80%99%20professional%20public%20management%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExplicit%20performance%20measures%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEmphasis%20on%20%E2%80%98output%20controls%E2%80%99%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECompetition%20in%20the%20public%20sector%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDisaggregation%20of%20units%20in%20the%20public%20sector%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStress%20on%20private%20sector%20styles%20of%20management%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20its%20introduction%2C%20spending%20on%20consultants%20increased%20dramatically.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20spending%20on%20consultants%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Defence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-6281.2009.00275.x%5C%22%3Efrom%201993%20to%202006%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%20from%20%C2%A355%20million%20to%20%C2%A3256%20million.%20Over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20spending%20by%20the%20Home%20Office%20increased%20from%20%C2%A33.81%20million%20to%20%C2%A3125%20million%20%E2%80%93%20a%20change%20of%203%2C190%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20public%20management%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%201980s%20when%20the%20economic%20ideas%20of%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20Margaret%20Thatcher%20and%20US%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20held%20sway.%20It%20represented%20a%20victory%20of%20private%20sector%20ideology%20over%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667641%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22679%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERonald%20Reagan%20with%20Margaret%20Thatcher.%20Photo%3A%20Unknown%20photographer%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20Public%20domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20underlying%20logic%20was%20that%20the%20private%20sector%20knows%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrivate%20sector%20management%20techniques%20were%20hypothetically%20introduced%20to%20produce%20better%20public%20sector%20outcomes.%20Whether%20new%20public%20management%20has%20done%20this%20or%20not%20remains%20a%20heated%20point%20of%20debate.%20At%20the%20very%20least%2C%20it%20has%20created%20an%20environment%20in%20which%20consultants%20can%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20been%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20expertise%20in%20government.%20As%20Professor%20Rod%20Rhodes%20described%20it%20many%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20state%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-923X.1994.tb00441.x%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98hollowed%20out%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20governments%20have%20turned%20to%20consultants%20more.%20However%2C%20this%20meant%20that%20public%20servants%20were%20not%20doing%20the%20necessary%20work%20to%20upgrade%20their%20skills%20and%20increase%20their%20expertise.%20The%20consultants%20were%20gaining%20that%20expertise%20and%20%E2%80%93%20for%20a%20fee%20%E2%80%93%20providing%20their%20advice%20to%20bureaucrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReliance%20on%20consultants%20became%20more%20and%20more%20entrenched%2C%20so%20now%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20consultants%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98shadow%E2%80%99%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20consultants%20on%20its%20own%20is%20not%20a%20problem.%20Decision%20makers%20throughout%20the%20ages%20have%20turned%20to%20advisors%20to%20assist%20with%20pressing%20challenges.%20Besides%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20governing%20today%20is%20far%20more%20complex%20than%20it%20was%20even%20a%20few%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20prudent%2C%20therefore%2C%20to%20turn%20to%20a%20range%20of%20different%20sources%20for%20advice%20%E2%80%93%20including%20consultants.%20And%20there%20are%20situations%20where%20very%20highly%20specialised%20or%20technical%20knowledge%20is%20required%20to%20support%20public%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20principle%20of%20consultants%20being%20part%20of%20governing%20today%20is%20sound%2C%20it%20is%20the%20practice%20that%20is%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20parts%20to%20this%20problem%3A%20definition%2C%20quantity%2C%20management%20and%20procurement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20definition%20relates%20to%20the%20public%20sector%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20of%20what%20consultants%20are%20and%20what%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20confusion%20as%20to%20how%20consultants%20differ%20from%20contractors%20and%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20how%20best%20to%20deploy%20them.%20This%20issue%20is%20fundamental%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20work%20that%20consultants%20are%20asked%20to%20do%20and%20how%20governments%20report%20on%20the%20extent%20of%20consultancy%20spending%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20work%20more%20appropriately%20classified%20as%20a%20contractor%20can%20be%20recorded%20as%20a%20consultancy%20(and%20vice-versa).%20It%20also%20means%20departments%20can%20pay%20a%20premium%20for%20the%20services%20of%20a%20consultant%20when%20a%20(much%20cheaper)%20contractor%20would%20suffice.%20It%20also%20might%20result%20in%20contractors%20putting%20up%20sub-standard%20work%2C%20thereby%20damaging%20the%20reputation%20of%20consultants%20generally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20quantity%20relates%20to%20how%20often%20governments%20use%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Victorian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.audit.vic.gov.au%2Fdashboards%2Fdepartments-reported-consultant-spend-2017-18-2021-22%5C%22%3EAuditor-General%E2%80%99s%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20estimated%20that%20the%20current%20Labor%20Government%20has%20spent%20(on%20average)%20AUD%24140%20million%20on%20consultants%20each%20year%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20If%20we%20assume%20that%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20a%20consulting%20project%20is%20AUD%24100%2C000%2C%20then%20that%20is%201%2C400%20consulting%20projects%20across%20the%20state%20government%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20140%20per%20department%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20large%2C%20this%20pales%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%E2%80%99s%20spend%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Ffeb%2F06%2Fministers-quietly-scrap-limits-on-whitehall-spending-on-consultants%5C%22%3E%C2%A32.8%20billion%20worth%20of%20consulting%20work%20in%202022%20alone.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20quantity%20is%20not%20just%20about%20%E2%80%98how%20much%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20also%20about%20%E2%80%98who%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20consulting%20work%20is%20often%20awarded%20to%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98Big%20Four%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20KPMG%2C%20Deloitte%2C%20PwC%20and%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young.%20The%20sheer%20volume%20of%20work%2C%20compounded%20with%20the%20awarding%20of%20work%20to%20a%20select%20group%20of%20firms%2C%20suggests%20the%20government%20is%20dependent%20on%20these%20specific%20firms.%20One%20UK%20official%20even%20warned%20others%20about%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F00076790500055756%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98addicted%20to%20having%20well%20trained%2C%20hard%20working%20people%20running%20around%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20management%20problem%20relates%20to%20poor%20supervision%20of%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDepartment%20officials%20sometimes%20see%20consulting%20work%20as%20%E2%80%98set-and-forget%E2%80%99%2C%20meaning%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20actively%20manage%20or%20take%20ownership%20of%20the%20process%20or%20the%20results.%20This%20may%20result%20in%20something%20that%20is%20not%20fit%20for%20purpose%2C%20meaning%20additional%20spending%20might%20be%20necessary%20to%20rectify%20a%20report%20or%20unwanted%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20can%20often%20be%20put%20in%20a%20position%20of%20power%20over%20their%20clients%20where%20the%20client%20does%20not%20necessarily%20understand%20the%20work%20the%20consultant%20is%20doing.%20Ideally%2C%20a%20consulting%20project%20should%20be%20co-owned%20by%20the%20bureaucrat%20and%20the%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20here%20is%20that%20bureaucrats%20end%20up%20defaulting%20to%20a%20consultant%20when%20internal%20staff%20might%20be%20more%20than%20capable%20of%20doing%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvpsc.vic.gov.au%2Fdata-and-research%2Fdata-facts-visuals-state-of-the-sector%2Femployment-arrangements-pay-grades-occupations%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20insecurity%20of%20public%20sector%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20sometimes%20mean%20consultants%20themselves%20become%20the%20keeper%20of%20institutional%20memory.%20If%20the%20right%20structures%20aren%E2%80%99t%20put%20in%20place%2C%20this%20can%20mean%20the%20expertise%20of%20the%20public%20sector%20is%20further%20eroded%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20consultants%20is%20made%20more%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09540962.2023.2184273%3FjournalCode%3Drpmm20%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAs%2520part%2520of%2520this%252C%2520we%2Cdynamics%2520are%2520maintained%2520and%2520expressed.%5C%22%3Eproblem%20of%20procurement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20traditional%20model%20assumes%20consulting%20services%20can%20be%20purchased%20just%20like%20any%20other%20good.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20purchasing%20consulting%20services%20is%20very%20different%20from%2C%20say%2C%20purchasing%20a%20piece%20of%20infrastructure.%20Consultants%20are%20often%20in%20relationships%20of%20co-dependency%20with%20government%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20relationships%20transcend%20individual%20transactions.%20However%2C%20the%20way%20in%20which%20procurement%20is%20practised%20often%20disguises%20these%20relationships%2C%20thus%20creating%20challenges%20in%20holding%20consultants%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccountability%20issues%20are%20further%20compounded%20given%20that%20consultants%20can%20often%20hide%20behind%20commercial-in-confidence%20privileges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%20issue%20we%20first%20need%20to%20rebuild%20the%20policy%20capacity%20of%20the%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20should%20only%20be%20called%20in%20when%20a%20task%20requires%20a%20highly%20specialised%20form%20of%20knowledge%20combined%20with%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%2C%20and%20relationships%20with%2C%20the%20specific%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20consultants%20could%20be%20required%20to%20upskill%20the%20public%20service%20in%20their%20processes%20and%20methodologies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fminerva-access.unimelb.edu.au%2Fitems%2F31f5b92a-27b1-5dec-9e6c-ba2435c92fd9%5C%22%3EAs%20this%20research%20demonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20does%20happen%2C%20though%20it%20might%20not%20be%20common%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternal%20consulting%20divisions%20within%20the%20government%20are%20a%20possibility.%20Interestingly%2C%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20current%20Labor%20Government%20has%20committed%20to%20doing%20just%20that%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20the%20UK%20Cabinet%20Office%20is%20shutting%20its%20down%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20real%20piece%20of%20work%20is%20long-term%20generational%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20career%20path%20for%20public%20servants%20and%20considering%20policy%20work%20a%20genuine%20profession%20can%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20involve%20better%20links%20between%20the%20public%20service%20and%20universities.%20It%20could%20see%20public%20departments%20define%20workforce%20needs%20and%20talk%20to%20universities%20directly%20about%20how%20those%20needs%20can%20be%20filled.%20It%20could%20consider%20public%20policy%20knowledge%20a%20genuine%20form%20of%20professional%20knowledge%20in%20its%20own%20right%20%E2%80%93%20similar%20to%20law%20or%20accounting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20going%20to%20require%20several%20years%20to%20get%20right.%20Largely%20because%20Australia%20is%20now%20trying%20to%20wind%20back%20several%20decades%20of%20neoliberal%20ideology%20%E2%80%93%20not%20something%20that%20can%20be%20done%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20servants%20could%20be%20trained%20in%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20work%20with%20consultants.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20consultants%20who%20want%20to%20work%20in%20government%20services%20could%20be%20required%20to%20undertake%20a%20professional%20accreditation%20that%20demonstrates%20they%20understand%20the%20important%20contextual%20differences%20between%20the%20public%20and%20private%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20procurement%20rules%20can%20be%20updated%20to%20remove%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98consulting%E2%80%99%20altogether.%20It%20causes%20too%20much%20confusion.%20Rather%2C%20categories%20could%20be%20based%20on%20the%20type%20of%20expertise%20that%20is%20actually%20being%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20governments%20often%20purchase%20evaluation%20services%2C%20but%20%E2%80%98evaluation%E2%80%99%20is%20not%20a%20recognised%20category%20in%20AusTender.%20Likewise%2C%20strategy%20advice%20or%20analytics%20are%20commonly-provided%20consulting%20services%20but%20are%20typically%20subsumed%20under%20the%20much%20broader%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98Management%20and%20Business%20Professionals%20and%20Administrative%20Services%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20very%20high-level%20categories%20can%20obscure%20as%20much%20as%20they%20reveal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20approach%20to%20procurement%20and%20the%20procurement%20rules%20applicable%20to%20consultants%20could%20also%20be%20overhauled%20to%20recognise%20the%20fundamentally%20relational%20%E2%80%93%20not%20transactional%20%E2%80%93%20ways%20in%20which%20consultants%20enter%20the%20public%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForms%20of%20%E2%80%98relational%20contracting%E2%80%99%20would%20be%20investigated%20to%20allow%20for%20more%20transparency%20in%20the%20ways%20consultants%20are%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultancies%20could%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20set%20of%20ethical%20rules%20and%20professional%20standards.%20Consulting%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%98look%20like%E2%80%99%20any%20other%20profession.%20There%20is%20no%20academic%20qualification%2C%20no%20professional%20standards%2C%20and%20no%20regulatory%20body%20for%20the%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20anybody%20can%20set%20up%20shop%20and%20call%20themselves%20a%20consultant.%20Addressing%20this%20issue%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20to%20ensuring%20money%20is%20spent%20appropriately%20and%20is%20providing%20quality%20outcomes%20to%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20role%20for%20consultants%20to%20play%20in%20modern%20systems%20of%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20lot%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20can%20rein%20in%20some%20of%20the%20excessive%20public%20expenditure%20on%20private%20forms%20of%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20several%20ideas%20that%20could%20be%20implemented%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20the%20real%20%E2%80%98fix%E2%80%99%20is%20moving%20away%20from%20ideologically%20privileging%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20recognise%20the%20unique%20value%20that%20public%20policy%20analysis%20and%20public%20servants%20can%20provide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20structural%20reform%20but%20a%20shift%20in%20perspective%20and%20culture.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20unscramble%20the%20omelette%2C%20but%20we%20can%20certainly%20make%20it%20taste%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20Marty%20Bortz%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3Eis%20an%20Honorary%20Senior%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Melbourne%20School%20of%20Government%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Melbourne.%20He%20has%20worked%20in%20local%20and%20state%20government%2C%20and%20private%20consulting%2C%20across%20multiple%20portfolios%20including%20education%2C%20health%2C%20justice%20and%20Indigenous%20affairs.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691742544000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11134930%2Fadriano-hhkJV1mbxw-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-shadow-government-plundering-the-public-purse%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20drive%20to%20privatise%20everything%20has%20led%20to%20consultants%20taking%20on%20the%20work%20of%20public%20servants.%20But%20at%20what%20cost%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-shadow-government-plundering-the-public-purse%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CAG%20Report%20Finds%20Irregularities%20in%20Ayodhya%20Development%20Project%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F29154416%2F1280px-Ayodhya_100_34.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20of%20India%20(CAG)%20has%20reportedly%20found%20irregularities%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20Ayodhya%20development%20plan%2C%20under%20the%20Swadesh%20Darshan%20Scheme.%20Irregularities%20include%20undue%20benefits%20to%20contractors%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fcag-undue-benefits-to-contractors-in-ayodhya-development-project-8886869%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20audited%20the%20Swadesh%20Darshan%20Scheme%20between%20January%202015%20to%20March%202022.%20The%20report%20from%20the%20audit%20was%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20stated%20that%20undue%20benefits%20of%20Rs%2019.73%20crore%20were%20made%20to%20contractors%20in%20six%20projects%2Fcircuits%20across%20six%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20undue%20benefits%20specific%20to%20the%20Ayodhya%20project%2C%20the%20CAG%20report%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20contractor%20engaged%20by%20the%20implementing%20agency%20viz.%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Rajkiya%20Nirman%20Nigam%2C%20was%20required%20to%20submit%20performance%20guarantee%20at%20the%20rate%20of%20five%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20contract%20price%20of%20Rs%2062.17%20crore%2C%20which%20worked%20out%20to%20Rs%203.11%20crore.%20However%2C%20the%20contractor%20submitted%20a%20lesser%20amount%20of%20performance%20guarantee%20i.e.%2C%20Rs%201.86%20crore%20only%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20its%20renewal%20(September%202021)%20without%20citing%20any%20reason%20on%20record.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWork%20at%20Guptar%20Ghat%2C%20Ayodhya%20was%20split%20into%2014%20lots%20of%20equal%20sizes%20and%20works%20were%20awarded%20to%20different%20private%20contractors.%20However%2C%20the%20executing%20agency%20(Irrigation%20Department)%20did%20not%20take%20due%20care%20in%20making%20comparative%20analysis%20of%20the%20financial%20bids%2Frates%20offered%20by%20the%20contractors%20and%20awarded%20works%20of%20similar%20nature%20and%20sanctioned%20costs%20to%20the%20same%20contractors%20but%20at%20varying%20rates%20resulting%20in%20failure%20to%20save%20Rs%2019.13%20lakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continued%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGST%20registrations%20of%20three%20contractors%20were%20cancelled%20by%20the%20state%20government%20suo%20motu%20after%20awarding%20of%20works%20to%20them.%20Thus%2C%20they%20were%20no%20more%20registered%20contractors%20and%20were%20not%20entitled%20to%20collect%20GST.%20However%2C%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2019.57%20lakh%20was%20irregularly%20paid%20to%20one%20contractor%20against%20his%20GST%20registration%20and%20in%20case%20of%20other%20two%20contractors%2C%20it%20was%20pending%20for%20payment%2C%20whereas%20full%20amount%20of%20GST%20was%20liable%20to%20be%20deducted%20and%20deposited%20by%20the%20executing%20agency%20(Irrigation%20Department)%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20CAG%20report%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContractors%20were%20paid%20for%20work%20that%20has%20not%20been%20executed%2C%20the%20CAG%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20work%20of%20development%20of%20the%20Guptar%20Ghat%20included%20work%20of%2023%2C767%20sq.mtr%20%E2%80%98supplying%20and%20fixing%20of%20stone%20patia%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20rate%20of%20Rs%201%2C447.50%20per%20sq.mtr.%20This%20work%20included%20the%20cost%20of%20MS%20clamp%20(supply%20and%20fixing)%20at%20Rs%20216.88%20per%20sq.mtr.%20(Rs%20136.88%20for%20supply%20and%20Rs%2080.00%20for%20fixing).%20The%20work%20was%20executed%20and%20payment%20was%20made%20to%20the%20private%20contractors%20at%20the%20rates%20quoted%20by%20them%20in%20their%20respective%20agreements%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20five%20projects%20mentioned%20in%20the%20report%20are%20the%20development%20of%20Sinquerim-Aguada%20Jail%2C%C2%A0Goa%3B%20Himalayan%20Circuit%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%3B%20Heritage%20Circuit%2C%20Telangana%3B%20development%20of%20Rangpo-Singtam%2C%20Sikkim%3B%20and%20Buddhist%20Circuit%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691740858000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F29154416%2F1280px-Ayodhya_100_34.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-finds-irregularities-in-ayodhya-development-project%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20says%20undue%20benefits%20were%20given%20to%20contractors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-finds-irregularities-in-ayodhya-development-project%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Provisions%20for%20sedition%20offences%20to%20be%20completely%20repealed%2C%20says%20Amit%20Shah%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691740601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F09%2Ffull%2F1691583494-7981.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fprovisions-for-sedition-offences-to-be-completely-repealed-says-amit-shah-123081100296_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shah%20also%20said%20that%20the%20provision%20of%20capital%20punishment%20will%20also%20be%20introduced%20in%20mob%20lynching%20cases%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fprovisions-for-sedition-offences-to-be-completely-repealed-says-amit-shah-123081100296_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fprovisions-for-sedition-offences-to-be-completely-repealed-says-amit-shah-123081100296_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fprovisions-for-sedition-offences-to-be-completely-repealed-says-amit-shah-123081100296_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%20and%20Mewat%3A%20On%20Reading%20Two%20Landscapes%20of%20Social%20Suffering%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09192254%2Fimage-1205.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pain%20of%20this%20beautiful%20land%20is%20widespread%20and%20seemingly%20unending.%20It%20touches%20us%20closely.%20Two%20members%20of%20our%20family%20are%20from%20Imphal%20and%20my%20niece%20is%20named%20after%20its%20river%2C%20Iril.%20In%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20I%20travelled%20several%20times%20through%20the%20state%2C%20always%20surprised%20at%20the%20levels%20of%20under%20development.%20Imphal%20did%20not%20even%20have%20a%20decent%20cafe%20or%20a%20book%20shop.%20As%20a%20historian-anthropologist%20of%20Mewat%2C%20I%20have%20also%20travelled%20in%20the%20villages%20and%20towns%20inhabited%20by%20the%20Indian%20Meos%20since%201985%20and%20seen%20closely%20the%20backwardness%20of%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20seven%20states%20of%20the%20northeast%2C%20a%20corrupt%20elite%20has%20constantly%20been%20siphoning%20off%20Central%20funds.%20Development%20continues%20to%20mean%20largely%20%E2%80%9Cinfrastructure.%E2%80%9D%20In%20Mewat%2C%20likewise%2C%20a%20Mewat%20Development%20Agency%2FBoard%20was%20set%20up%20but%20during%20my%20fieldwork%20I%20heard%20numerous%20complaints%20that%20instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20the%20entrenched%20backwardness%20of%20the%20Meo%20community%2C%20its%20funds%20were%20utilised%20largely%20for%20building%20roads%2C%20which%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20the%20task%20of%20the%20Public%20Works%20Department%20(PWD).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20roots%20of%20the%20problem%20run%20deep.%20Colonialism%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20Mizoram%20simultaneously%20introduced%20writing%2C%20the%20state%20and%20the%20modern%20idea%20of%20religion.%20Ethnology%20sought%20to%20map%20racial%20distinctions%20and%20Christian%20missionaries%20converted%20peoples%20whom%20colonial%20knowledge%20had%20classified%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctribals%E2%80%9D%20and%20people%20without%20religion.%20Among%20the%20Nagas%2C%20the%20British%20created%20an%20aspiration%20for%20a%20Greater%20Nagaland%2C%20thinking%20of%20this%20as%20a%20continuing%20foothold%20for%20themselves%20even%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20would%20be%20decolonised.%20The%20latest%20missionaries%20are%20those%20attempting%20to%20spread%20a%20packaged%20Hinduism%2C%20as%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20Missionaries%20also%20appear%20in%20secular%20guise%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Ulfa-Maoist%20alliance%20responsible%20for%20the%20killing%20of%20Sanjoy%20Ghose%20in%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Manipur%2C%20nationalism%20was%20particularly%20strong%20and%20rallied%20around%20the%20figure%20of%20the%20king.%20Its%20backbone%20was%20the%20major%20community%20of%20the%20Meitei%2C%20which%20had%20come%20under%20the%20influence%20of%20Vaishnava%20Hindu%20practice%20and%20created%20a%20culture%20richly%20endowed%20with%20music%20and%20dance%2C%20literature%20and%20theatre.%20It%20is%20supremely%20ironic%20that%20this%20community%20came%20to%20spawn%20a%20large%20number%20of%20terror%20organisations%20in%20postcolonial%20India.%20Why%20this%20came%20to%20be%20so%20is%20a%20question%20that%20should%20have%20been%20asked%20by%20all%20Indians.%20Both%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20Manipur%2C%20the%20footprint%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20(Special%20Powers)%20Act%20was%20the%20largest%20and%20spawned%20the%20spiral%20of%20violence%20and%20counter-violence%20fostered%20also%20by%20the%20supply%20of%20arms%C2%A0%20from%20China%20and%20Burma%20to%20terror%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20closely%20followed%20the%20story%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20protest%20against%20the%20Indian%20army%20and%20read%20during%20a%20long%20stay%20in%20Imphal%20Teresa%20Rehman%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Mothers%20of%20Manipu%3C%2Fem%3Er%3Cem%3E%3A%20The%20Twelve%20Women%20who%20Made%20History%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebased%20on%20her%20moving%20interviews%20of%20how%20women%20responded%20to%20the%20rape%20of%20Manorama%20in%20July%202004.%20At%20a%20tense%20meeting%20held%20in%20a%20closed%20room%20in%20the%20Ima%20Keithel%20women%E2%80%99s%20market%2C%20a%20dozen%20women%20agreed%20to%20strip%20naked%20and%20hold%20up%20a%20banner%20with%20the%20words%2C%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Army%20rape%20us%E2%80%99.%20The%20protest%20was%20kept%20absolutely%20secret%20even%20from%20their%20husbands%20and%20families%20and%20some%20even%20fainted%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20protest%20held%20outside%20the%20gate%20of%20the%20Kangla%20Fort.%20The%20Army%20commander%20eventually%20came%20out%20and%20bowed%20before%20the%20women.%20On%20November%2020%2C%202004%2C%20the%20fort%20%E2%80%93%20a%20symbol%20of%20Manipuri%20nationalism%20%E2%80%93%20was%20handed%20back%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Manipur.%20King%20Khagemba%20(1597-1652)%20had%20built%20this%20fort%20where%20the%20universe%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20centred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20to%20digest%20that%20in%202023%20women%20used%20themselves%20as%20human%20shields%20in%20the%20pitched%20battles%20between%20Kuki%20and%20Meitei%20gangs.%20There%20are%20many%20factors%20that%20have%20created%20this%20round%20of%20violence.%20The%20Meitei%20demand%20is%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20status%20that%20seeks%20for%20the%20community%20the%20benefits%20of%20affirmative%20action%20and%20the%20right%20to%20buy%20land%20in%20the%20hill%20areas.%20Currently%2C%20Kukis%20can%20buy%20land%20in%20the%20valley%20but%20the%20Meitei%20do%20not%20have%20the%20reciprocal%20right%20and%20feel%20that%20the%20valley%20is%20getting%20crowded.%20The%20land%20in%20the%20hills%20is%20mineral%20rich.%20Finally%2C%20there%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-violence-poppy-national-security-golden-triangle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erole%20of%20the%20drug%20lords%20in%20collaboration%20with%20actors%20at%20various%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20in%20the%20larger%20region%20known%20as%20the%20Golden%20Triangle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20Nuh%20conflict%20likewise%20has%20two%20centuries%20of%20colonial%20rule%20behind%20it%2C%20particularly%20the%20play%20of%20the%20categories%20of%20caste%20and%20religion%2C%20which%20continue%20to%20colonise%20contemporary%20India.%20In%20the%20census%20you%20could%20be%20either%20Hindu%20or%20Muslim%2C%20not%20both%20simultaneously%2C%20which%20would%20have%20been%20the%20closest%20approximation%20to%20Meo%20practice%2C%20as%20indeed%2C%20they%20venerated%20both%20Sufi%20saints%20and%20Shiva%2FMahadeva.%20Over%20a%20period%2C%20the%20number%20of%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20Mewatis%E2%80%9D%20shrunk%20and%20then%20disappeared%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENuh%2C%20Taoru%2C%20Nagina%2C%20Punhana%20and%20Ferozepur%20Jhirka%2C%20the%20five%20blocks%20of%20Haryana%E2%80%99s%20district%20of%20Nuh%20(created%20in%202013)%20have%20been%20among%20the%20poorest%20areas%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Punjab.%20These%20were%20the%20drylands%20of%20low%20productivity%20exacerbated%20by%20cycles%20of%20famine%20and%20stringent%20colonial%20revenue%20collection.%20Little%20wonder%20that%20anti-colonial%20feeling%20was%20particularly%20high%20among%20the%20Meos.%20Insurgency%20affected%20both%20the%20Rajasthan%20and%20Punjab%20areas%20of%20Mewat%20in%201857%20and%20the%20British%20made%20the%20Meos%20pay%20for%20it.%20Subsequent%20state%20investment%20in%20canals%20was%20largely%20in%20areas%20inhabited%20by%20the%20Jats%2C%20seen%20as%20the%20stolid%20Victorian%20peasants%2C%20but%20rendered%20both%20Meo%20and%20Gujjar%20villages%20significantly%20impoverished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20media%20reports%20highlight%20the%20high%20fertility%20rate%20of%20the%20Meos%20of%20Nuh%20and%20also%20their%20backwardness%20in%20terms%20of%20female%20literacy%20but%20ignore%20the%20other%20components%20of%20backwardness%20such%20as%20the%20declining%20political%20representation%20of%20the%20Meos%20compared%20with%20other%20backward%20caste%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Jats%20and%20Yadavs.%20This%20was%20a%20result%20partly%20of%20the%20partition%20exodus%20of%20the%20Meos%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20genocidal%20violence%20of%20the%20princely%20states%20of%20Alwar%20and%20Bharatpur%20in%20alliance%20with%20a%20new%20social%20formation%2C%20a%20notorious%20intercaste%20coalition%20called%20AJGAR%2C%20its%20constituents%20being%20Ahirs%2C%20Jats%20and%20Gujars%20who%20had%20for%20centuries%20lived%20peacefully%20with%20the%20Meos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hunger%20for%20land%20was%20tremendous%20among%20these%20peasant%20groups%20and%20what%20better%20excuse%20to%20decimate%20the%20Meos%20and%20cause%20them%20to%20migrate%20than%20the%20Muslim%20League%20movement%20for%20Pakistan.%20It%20did%20not%20matter%20that%20the%20Meo%20leadership%20was%20largely%20pro-Congress%20and%20against%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20League%20and%20the%20movement%20for%20Pakistan.%20They%20could%20and%20were%20accused%20of%20creating%20a%20Meoistan%20analogous%20to%20Pakistan!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20before%20Partition%2C%20a%20new%2C%20hyper-nationalist%20popular%20history%20had%20been%20created%20that%20constructed%20the%20Meos%20as%20exclusively%20Muslim.%20This%20new%20history%20is%20postulated%20on%20forgetting%2C%20an%20erasure%20of%20the%20past.%20The%20Meos%20had%20been%20regarded%20by%20the%20British%20as%20half-Hindu%3B%20they%20shared%20in%20the%20practices%20of%20pastoral-agrarian%20culture%20such%20as%20the%20jajmani%20patronage%20of%20dependent%20castes%3B%20a%20kinship%20system%20in%20which%20cross-cousin%20marriage%20(what%20they%20call%20%3Cem%3Ekaka-tau%20mein%20nikah%3C%2Fem%3E)%20was%20anathema%3B%20the%20seasonal%20cycles%20of%20festivals%20and%20pilgrimages%20to%20Krishna%E2%80%99s%20Govardhan%20Yatra%20%E2%80%93%20after%20all%2C%20Krishna%20was%20the%20progenitor%20of%20the%20Meo%20Jadu%20clans%2C%20as%20Rama%20was%20of%20the%20Meo%20Badgujar%20clans%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20the%20Mahadeva%20shrine%20in%20the%20hills%20for%20it%20was%20always%20Shiva%20who%20came%20to%20assist%20them%20at%20moments%20of%20crisis%20and%20in%20their%20struggle%20with%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20history%20of%20the%20Meos%20as%20cow%20killers%20also%20ignores%20the%20massive%20effort%20at%20cow%20protection%20by%20the%20Meo%20panchayats%3B%20that%20many%20Meos%20kept%20cows%20and%20that%20many%20Meo%20women%20would%20craft%20stacks%20of%20cowdung%20cakes%20with%20floral%20designs.%20In%20the%20Mewati%20Mahabharata%20the%20five%20Pandava%20brothers%20graze%20cows%20while%20their%20shared%20wife%2C%20Draupadi%2C%20is%20an%20incarnation%20of%20the%20goddess%2C%20capable%20of%20the%20curse%20of%20great%20destruction%20that%20will%20be%20wrought%20on%20the%20Kaurava%20army%20after%20she%20is%20publicly%20disrobed%20in%20Duryodhana%E2%80%99s%20court!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20Mewat%20has%20been%20whiplashed%20by%20violence%20again%20and%20again.%20The%20most%20recent%20phase%20began%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20has%20been%20fuelled%20by%20the%20VHP%20and%20the%20Bajrang%20Dal.%20Acharya%20Dharmendra%2C%20one%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20the%20Dharma%20Sansad%2C%20once%20told%20me%20that%20Mewat%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccold%E2%80%9D%20area%20(read%3A%20where%20inter-communal%20violence%20has%20been%20relatively%20less).%20Cow%20killing%20became%20the%20cry%20against%20the%20Meos%20as%20the%20VHP%20intensified%20the%20heat%2C%20creating%20crisis%20after%20crisis%20in%20the%20Bharatpur%2C%20Alwar%20districts%20of%20Rajasthan%20and%20then%20in%20Haryana%E2%80%99s%20Mewat%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Nuh%20and%20Gurgaon%2FGurugram%20have%20been%20host%20to%20cow%20vigilante%20groups%20and%20episodes%20of%20lynching%2C%20the%20public%20executions%20carried%20out%20by%20vigilante%20groups%20in%20the%20name%20of%20cow%20protection.%20Asif%20Khan%20of%20Khalilpur%20Kheda%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fasif-khan-lynched-mewat-haryana-police-arrests-accused%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elynched%20by%20a%20mob%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20he%20was%20returning%20from%20buying%20medicine%3B%20Nasir%20and%20Junaid%20were%20allegedly%20attacked%20and%20abducted%20in%20February%202023.%20According%20to%20the%20chargesheet%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20police%2C%20the%20Haryana%20police%20refused%20to%20register%20a%20case%20against%20them%2C%20after%20which%20their%20bodies%20were%20set%20ablaze%20by%20a%20gang%20said%20to%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fjunaid-nasir-murder-chargesheet-rinku-saini-monu-manesar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvolved%20with%20Bajrang%20Dal%20leader%2C%20Mohit%20Yadav%20known%20as%20Monu%20Manesar.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20preparation%20for%20the%20latest%20round%20of%20violence%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20new%20procession%20devised%20three%20years%20ago%20to%20a%20temple.%20Videos%20were%20circulated%2C%20announcing%20the%20presence%20of%20gangsters%20Monu%20Manesar%20and%20Bijju%20Bajrangi.%20According%20to%20press%20reports%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DfI4crZ2ZE_Q%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintelligence%20report%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%20but%20not%20passed%20on%20to%20the%20home%20minister%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20likewise%20no%20action%20was%20taken%20by%20the%20police%20following%20an%20alert%20by%20the%20Nuh%20Peace%20Committee.%20A%20deliberately%20circulated%20rumour%20of%20the%20arrival%20of%20Monu%20Manesar%20in%20a%20vehicle%20led%20to%20stone%20pelting%20by%20Meos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20all%20shops%20and%20businesses%20in%20Gurgaon%20were%20asked%20to%20remove%20Muslims%20from%20the%20premises%20else%20they%20would%20be%20treated%20as%20traitors.%20Within%20days%20Muslims%20including%20cobblers%2C%20tailors%20and%20labour%20fled%20from%20four%20districts%20of%20the%20Haryana%20State.%20The%20only%20exception%20were%20the%20Bengalis%20as%20without%20them%20Gurgaon%E2%80%99s%20services%20would%20collapse.%20The%20bulldozer%20then%20began%20its%20work%2C%20razing%20the%20homes%20of%20Nuh%20residents%C2%A0%20until%20it%20was%20called%20to%20a%20halt%20by%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20defined%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20as%20a%20land%20of%20communities.%20Living%20together%2C%20rural%20and%20urban%20socialites%20have%20been%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20its%20civilisation%20for%20several%20millennia.%20Is%20this%20fabric%20coming%20asunder%20is%20a%20question%20all%20Indians%20must%20ask%20themselves%20today.%20If%20so%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20recognise%20the%20sources%20of%20violence%20through%20deep%20readings%20of%20the%20past%20as%20a%20prelude%20to%20action.%20The%20present%20scenario%20looks%20bleak%20with%20only%20institutions%20such%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20a%20bulwark%20for%20Manipur%20and%20the%20inter-communal%20mobilisation%20of%20the%20Kisan%20Movement%20as%20a%20ray%20of%20hope%20in%20Mewat%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShail%20Mayaram%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Secret%20Life%20of%20Another%20Indian%20Nationalism%3A%20Transitions%20from%20the%20Pax%20Britannica%20to%20the%20Pax%20Americana%3Cem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Cambridge%20University%20Press.%20She%20is%20an%20honorary%20fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20in%20Delhi.%20She%20is%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Academic%20Advisory%20Board%20at%20the%20K%C3%A4te%20Hamburger%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Apocalyptic%20and%20Postapocalyptic%20Studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Heidelberg.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691740337000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09192254%2Fimage-1205.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmanipur-and-mewat-on-reading-two-landscapes-of-social-suffering%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20was%20defined%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98land%20of%20communities%E2%80%99.%20But%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20and%20Mewat%20makes%20us%20question%20whether%20this%20fabric%20is%20breaking%20apart.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmanipur-and-mewat-on-reading-two-landscapes-of-social-suffering%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20launches%20first%20moon%20mission%20in%20almost%2050%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691740260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-soyuz-russia-rocket_6247134.jpg%3F20230811080427%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frussia-launches-first-moon-mission-in-almost-50-years-12937743%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20has%20launched%20its%20first%20moon%20mission%20in%20almost%2050%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A114%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frussia-launches-first-moon-mission-in-almost-50-years-12937743%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Frussia-launches-first-moon-mission-in-almost-50-years-12937743%22